.TH "git alias.mergefrom(1) User manual" "" "April, 2020" "" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
git mergefrom
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
git mergefrom branch - stow working copy, merge with first argument,
then unstow
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
git mergefrom is a helper alias to merge another branch onto HEAD.
.IP "1." 3
Ensures that the current HEAD is not a detached HEAD
.IP "2." 3
Ensures that the proper number of arguments have been provided
.IP "3." 3
Stores the ref of HEAD so it can be returned to later
.IP "4." 3
Ensures that the provided argument is associated with a branch
.IP "5." 3
Calls the stow alias to temporarily store the Workspace
.IP "6." 3
Executes the merge
.IP "7." 3
Calls the \[oq]unstow\[oq]\ alias to restore the Workspace to its former
condition
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
git mergefrom branch
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
mergeto finishfrom rebasefrom
.SH DETAILS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
mergefrom = \[dq]!f() { : git man mergefrom; \[rs]
    if ! git symbolic-ref HEAD; then echo \[aq]on detached head\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    [ $# -ne 1 ] && echo \[aq]Usage: mergefrom branch\[aq] && return 1; \[rs]
    PREV=$(git symbolic-ref HEAD | cut -d/ -f3-); \[rs]
    if ! git rev-parse --abbrev-ref $1; then echo \[aq]branch not a named ref\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    if ! git stow; then return 1; fi; \[rs]
    if ! git merge $1; then git mt; git commit; fi; \[rs]
    git unstow; \[rs]
}; f\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
